---
title: Countryside Chicken Legs with Green Beans Amandine and Chive Mashed Potatoes
description: When it comes to chicken, we’re always looking for two things: golden crackly skin and juicy, flavorful meat. Enter: these French-style roasted chicken legs. They’re all that and then some—the “some” being floral Herbes de Provence and a tangy mustard dressing that really takes ’em above and beyond. They’re served alongside almond-flecked green beans and chive mashed potatoes so you can...get a LEG up on dinnertime!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/countryside-chicken-legs-ce67cc60.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/countryside-chicken-legs-5de6dd6e9f54e2148c123f96-2e58a86d.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: French
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/countryside-chicken-legs-5de6dd6e9f54e2148c123f96
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 390 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Pat @chicken legs{16%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; rub each chicken leg with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} and season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Herbes de Provence{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4; we sent more). Place skin sides up on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Bake on top rack for ~{20%minutes} (we'll add more to the sheet then).

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1} (quarter both lemons for 4 servings). Mince @chives{1/4%ounce}. Pick @tarragon{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems and mince leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4). Minc or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced); leave remaining clove whole.

Place potatoes and whole garlic clove in a medium #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Cover to keep warm.

Once chicken has roasted 20 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Toss @green beans{6%ounce} on empty side of same baking sheet with a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, leave chicken roasting and toss green beans on a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.

Return to oven until green beans are tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes} more. Toss roasted green beans with @almonds{1/2%ounce} and lemon zest to taste.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, tarragon, half the chives, and as much minced garlic and lemon juice as you like. Stir in @olive oil{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a pinch of @sugar{}.

Mash potatoes with @sour cream{2%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed with a #potato masher{}. Stir in remaining chives and season with salt and pepper. Divide chicken, green beans, and mashed potatoes between plates. Spoon dressing over chicken. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.